The shrimps shall inherit the earth.

Chen I.

A new report confirms that peewees outlast titans--among rodents, at least. 
Whereas most studies assess size at one time point or life stage, the new one 
tracks the rodents' weight month by month from birth to death. As a result, the 
work offers the first hint that body weight at an early age correlates with an 
animal's life expectancy.

